LEASE AGREEMENT
This Lease Agreement (Agreement) is made and entered into as of December 20, 2024 (Effective Date), by and between Roadrunner BESS SF LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (Lessor) and Roadrunner Battery Storage LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (Lessee). Lessor and Lessee are sometimes referred to herein each individually as a Party and collectively as the Parties.
A. Lessor is a wholly owned subsidiary of Roadrunner Battery Storage LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (Roadrunner BatteryCo), and a party to the Shared Facilities Agreement (SFA), dated as of the Effective Date, with Roadrunner Solar SF LLC, a Delaware limited liability company (SF 1), under which Lessor owns its Undivided Interest in the Shared Facilities and Lessor holds its Percentage Interest in the real property rights to the Shared Premises pursuant to the Shared Premises Agreements (as defined in the SFA). The SFA is evidenced by a Memorandum of Shared Facilities Agreement dated as of the Effective Date by and among Lessor and SF 1 recorded in the official public records for real property of Cochise County, Arizona.
B. Lessee is developing an approximately 235 Mwac/940 MWh battery energy storage facility on real property located in Cochise County, Arizona that will include photovoltaic modules, inverters, and associated collection and interconnection lines and related facilities and improvements (the Project), which requires the use of Shared Facilities and Shared Premises.
C. Pursuant to the SFA and as set forth above, Lessor desires to lease to Lessee, and Lessee desires to lease from Lessor, all of Lessors rights and obligations in and to its respective Undivided Interest and its Percentage Interest.
NOW, THEREFORE, in consideration of the foregoing and for other good and valuable consideration, the receipt and sufficiency of which are hereby acknowledged, and intending to be legally bound hereby, Lessor and Lessee hereby agree as follows:
1. Definitions. Unless otherwise defined herein, capitalized terms shall have the meanings given to them in the SFA. This Agreement is the Applicable Agreement, the Project is the Applicable Project, and Lessee is the Applicable Project Company with respect to SF 1 under the SFA.
2. Lease. Lessor leases to Lessee, and Lessee leases from Lessor, its Undivided Interest and Percentage Interest, subject to the terms of the SFA, the Shared Premises Agreements and this Agreement; provided, however, that such lease shall be limited to the rights comprising such Undivided Interest and Percentage Interest for the development, construction, ownership, operation, and maintenance of the Project. Without limiting the generality of the foregoing in this Section 2, Lessee acknowledges and agrees that (a) all of Lessees rights, title and interest under this Agreement are limited to the use of all of Lessors rights, title and interest in Lessors Undivided Interest and Percentage Interest, subject to the terms of the SFA, the Shared Premises Agreements and this Agreement, (b) Lessee has no right to use any other Co- Tenants rights under the SFA, the Shared Assets, or the Shared Premises Agreements, (c) Lessee approves of the SFA and agrees to comply with any obligations or liabilities of Lessor or Lessee under the SFA and with respect to such Undivided Interest, Percentage Interest or the Project under the SFA or the Shared Premises Agreements, including Sections 3.3, 3.4, 3.5, 3.7, 5.3, 6.1, 6.3, 6.4, 6.7, 6.9, and 6.10, Articles 12 and 13 and Exhibit C of the SFA, (d) Lessee shall perform its obligations under the Large Generator Interconnection Agreement Co-Tenancy Agreement, dated as of the date hereof, among Lessee, Roadrunner BatteryCo, and SF 1, and (e) Lessee is to provide to Lessor such information and documentation in its, its Affiliates or their respective Representatives control or possession that is required, and in a timely manner, for Lessor to comply with the SFA.
1 Docusign Envelope ID: 5F8783FD-559A-46EF-A7B0-4208ED99724F
3. Act per Instructions.
(a) Subject to the terms of this Agreement, Lessor shall perform its obligations and exercise its rights and obligations, and the rights and obligations of Lessee, under the SFA for the benefit of Lessee, in accordance with any oral or written instructions delivered by Lessee (Instructions). Unless otherwise provided in this Agreement, Lessor shall make each election, cast each vote, make each decision and take each action under the SFA in accordance with Lessees Instructions, including with respect to the following matters: (i) procurement, installation or construction of the Shared Assets or issuing any notice to proceed under any engineering, procurement and construction agreement with respect thereto; (ii) installation or approval of any Additional Shared Assets; (iii) review or approval of the FERC Filing (as defined in the SFA), if any; (iv) incurring costs, expenses or other Liabilities related to the Interconnection Agreement (except as otherwise required by the SFA); (v) incurring or paying any Shared Expenses, or propose additional categories or types of expenses to be Shared Expenses, or incur or pay any other expenditures in connection with the SFA (except as otherwise required by the SFA); (vi) designate the Shared Facilities Representative and the Manager Representative, if applicable; (vii) take any action or make any payment with respect to any claim for indemnification, defense or hold harmless or contribution in connection therewith; (viii) elect to cure or dispute any Event of Default (as defined in the SFA); (ix) elect to remove or approve of the Manager; (xi) approve any Annual Shared Facilities Budget and (x) exercise any right to request any action by the Manager or other Co-Tenant in accordance with the SFA.
(b) Subject to the terms of this Agreement, Lessor shall not take any of the following actions under the SFA without the written approval of Lessee: (i) any action that requires the consent or approval of Lessor or Lessee under the SFA, including any approval of a claim for indemnification, defense (including control over the defense thereunder), hold harmless or contribution under Article 11 of the SFA or any Major Decision or any action provided in Section 8.3 of the SFA; provided, however, that, if Lessor is responsible, without a right to reimbursement from Lessee, with respect to any Liability associated therewith, Lessor shall be permitted to elect such consent or approval acting reasonably; (ii) relinquish its interest and cease to be a Co-Tenant under the SFA; (iii) except as otherwise provided in this Agreement, create or cause to be created any Lien on the Undivided Interests or Percentage Interests or otherwise prohibited by the SFA; (iv) any action that would intentionally prevent the development, construction or operation of, otherwise result in an impairment to, the Project or any Project Specific Assets for the Project; (v) except as otherwise provided in this Agreement or the SFA, Transfer all or any portion of the Undivided Interests or Percentage Interest of Lessor; (vi) except as contemplated by Section 15, borrow funds or otherwise incur indebtedness, or act as a surety, grant guarantees or incur similar liabilities on behalf of third parties, directly or indirectly, whether for borrowed money or otherwise; (vii) amend, modify, change, waive, or grant forbearance of any term of the SFA or any Shared Premises Agreement, in any material respect, or agree to terminate the SFA or any Shared Premises Agreement; (viii) change the capacity of the Shared Assets; (ix) make any election with respect to a Restoration Proposal; (x) intentionally incur any expense that is not in accordance with the Approved Shared Facilities Budget or otherwise required by the SFA (except to the extent such expense is required to address an Emergency); (xi) compromise or settle any litigation or arbitration involving the Shared Assets or the SFA; or (xii) intentionally take any other action that would cause a breach of or default under the SFA.
(c) Prior to making any election or decision, casting any vote or taking any action under the SFA, Lessor shall timely provide Lessee all relevant and material information and documents in its, its Affiliates or any of their respective Representatives possession with respect to such election, decision, vote or action and request for Lessees Instruction with respect thereto. Lessor shall, from time to time, provide, or cause to be provided, to Lessee any governmental notices (including, without limitation, notice of any proposed condemnation proceeding, zoning change or alleged legal, regulatory or other noncompliance relating to the Shared Premises), material information and material matters in its, its Affiliates or any of their respective Representatives possession occurring under or in connection with the
2 Docusign Envelope ID: 5F8783FD-559A-46EF-A7B0-4208ED99724F
SFA, and shall respond promptly to any reasonable inquiries and information requests from Lessee. If Lessee fails to provide any instruction or an Emergency exists, and such failure or Emergency, as applicable, could, as determined in good faith by Lessor, result in an adverse effect on the Project, the Shared Assets or Lessee or under the SFA, any Shared Premises Agreement, the Interconnection Agreement or any applicable power purchase or storage agreement, Lessor shall be permitted to act in good faith under the circumstances with respect to the subject matter of such instruction.
(d) Notwithstanding the foregoing in this Section 3, Lessor shall not be required to take any action that is prohibited by applicable Law, could result in injury to persons or property, could result in any breach or default under, Liability under, or other adverse effect under or on any contract, the Shared Assets, any other Co-Tenant or any other Project Company; provided, however, that this Section 3(d) shall not apply to any Liability that is reimbursable by Lessee and does not fall within any other category described in this Section 3(d).
(e) Lessor shall not be subject to an Event of Default due to following any Instruction.
4. Rent and Reimbursement.
(a) Lessee shall pay to Lessor $1,000.00 per calendar month (Base Amount), commencing on the date the Project is synchronized with the grid under the Interconnection Agreement (Commencement Date) and for each calendar month thereafter; provided, however, that subject to the consent requirements of Section 4.3(a) of the SFA, the Base Amount may be increased by Lessor to reflect an amortized portion of any Increased Contract Price payable pursuant to the Shared Facilities EPC. The first such Base Amount payment shall be due on the Commencement Date and shall be due for each subsequent calendar month on or before the fifth day of such calendar month (pro rated for any partial month during the Term on a day-for-day basis). As used herein, the term Increased Contract Price shall mean any increase in the Contract Price (as such term is defined in the Shared Facilities EPC) above the amount of the Contract Price as of the Effective Date.
(b) Lessee shall reimburse Lessor for documented and out-of-pocket expenses incurred by Lessor in connection with this Agreement, the SFA and the Shared Premises Agreement, including the following (to the extent applicable); provided, however, that Lessee shall not be required to reimburse Lessor for (A) Lessors normal overhead-related expenses, or (B) expenses incurred as a result of gross negligence or willful misconduct by Lessor:
(i) Lessors share of the Shared Expenses;
(ii) Lessors share of the Construction Costs or Applicable Construction Costs or any reimbursement therefor;
(iii) Taxes with respect to the Undivided Interest or Shared Premises owned by Lessor in accordance with Section 6.2 of the SFA;
(iv) The cost of maintaining any insurance required under Article 12 of the SFA;
(v) Removal Costs or Withdrawal Costs, if any;
(vi) Any Liability required to be reimbursed by Lessor to the Manager or other Co- Tenants under the SFA or required for the performance of Lessors obligations under the SFA, Shared Premises Agreement or this Agreement, including any Liability in connection with Article 11 of the SFA or Section 3.7, 4.1, 4.3, 4.4, 6.3,
3 Docusign Envelope ID: 5F8783FD-559A-46EF-A7B0-4208ED99724F
6.12, 6.13(b), 8.12.2, 14.3 or 14.4 of the SFA (whether for indemnification, contribution, reimbursement or otherwise); and
(vii) Any other costs expended with respect to the Project or the Project Specific Assets of Lessee.
On or before the tenth day of each month, Lessor shall submit to the Lessee an invoice of expenses incurred by Lessor during the preceding month to be reimbursed pursuant to this Section 4(b), which invoice shall be accompanied by reasonable supporting documentation showing amounts properly due and payable and copies of the underlying invoices and supporting materials, as applicable. Any amounts due pursuant to an invoice shall be due and payable 15 days following receipt of such invoice by Lessee. Lessee shall have the right to audit any expenses or other amounts required to be paid by Lessee pursuant to this Section 4(b). If there is a Dispute as to any amount invoiced by Lessor, then Lessee shall pay all amounts not in Dispute in accordance with this Section 4. Any Disputes with respect to any amount invoiced by Lessor shall be resolved in accordance with the provisions of Section 19(c). Lessee shall pay any disputed amount ultimately determined as payable with interest thereon at the Default Rate accruing from the date of receipt of the Lessors disputed invoice.
(c) All payments made by a Party under this Section 4 shall be made by electronic funds transfer or wire transfer in immediately available funds in the currency set forth in the applicable invoice for receipt by the due date to the account specified in such invoice under which a payment is being made.
(d) If Lessor receives any refunds or monies that are attributable to expenses paid by a Lessee hereunder and such refunds or monies are not reimbursed to Lessee under another agreement with Lessee or any Liabilities with respect to the Project, Lessor shall promptly pay such refunds or monies to Lessee, including any amounts contemplated by Section 3.7 or 4.1 or Article 11 of the SFA.
(e) If Lessee fails to timely pay any amount due hereunder, such amount shall bear interest at the Default Rate.
5. Project and Ownership.
(a) Subject to the Security Documents and this Agreement, Lessor and Lessee hereby each acknowledge and agree that (i) Lessee is and shall remain the exclusive owner and operator of the Project, and if Lessee Transfers any interest in the Project, Lessee shall require the transferee thereof to assume Lessees rights and obligations under this Agreement and (ii) the Shared Facilities shall not be Transferred with the fee interest or leasehold or other rights in or to the Shared Premises or the Project Site or otherwise by Lessor or Lessee, as applicable. Security Documents means (A) the Pledge Agreement, between Roadrunner BatteryCo and Lessee, (B) the Security Agreement, between Lessor and Lessee, and (C) the Mortgage, between Lessor and Lessee, in each case, to be entered into on or about the date of financial close for the Project.
(b) Lessor shall not directly or indirectly cause or create any Lien on or with respect to the Project or any interest therein; provided, however, that this Section 5(b) shall not limit any obligation or liability, or any Lien, in connection with this Agreement. If Lessor breaches its obligations under this Section, Lessor shall immediately notify Lessee in writing, shall promptly cause such liens to be discharged and released of record without cost to Lessee, and shall indemnify Lessee against all costs and expenses (including reasonable attorneys fees and court costs at trial and on appeal) incurred in discharging and releasing such Liens.
4 Docusign Envelope ID: 5F8783FD-559A-46EF-A7B0-4208ED99724F
6. Access. Lessee shall have access to the Shared Facilities and Shared Premises in accordance with Section 3.4 of the SFA. Lessee, following at least two days advance written or telephonic notice from Lessor, shall (a) permit Lessor and its representatives to have access to enter the Project Site during regular business hours, for the purposes of inspecting the Project Site or for complying with any applicable Law, and (b) permit Lessor, at reasonable times, to show the Project Site during normal business hours to any existing or prospective lender with respect to the Project; provided, however, that Lessor shall not damage the Project or disrupt or disturb the operation of the Project. Lessee shall have the right to be present during any such access to the Project Site by Lessor and Lessee shall have the right to approve (which approval shall not be unreasonably withheld, delayed or conditioned) any repair, maintenance or other work at the Project Site which could affect the Project or the operation thereof.
7. Representations and Warranties and Covenants.
(a) Representations and Warranties. Each Party represents and warrants, as of the Effective Date, that (i) such Party is duly formed, validly existing and in good standing under the laws of its jurisdiction of formation and Lessor is in good standing under the laws of the State of Arizona, (ii) such Party has the organizational power and authority to execute and deliver this Agreement and to perform its obligations under this Agreement, (iii) the execution, delivery and performance by such Party of this Agreement have been duly authorized and approved by all necessary organizational action by such Party, (iv) this Agreement has been executed and delivered by such Party and constitutes the valid and binding obligation of such Party, enforceable against it in accordance with its terms, except as such enforcement may be limited by bankruptcy, insolvency or other similar laws affecting the enforcement of creditors rights generally and except that the availability of equitable remedies is subject to the discretion of the court before which any proceeding therefore may be brought, and (v) none of the execution, delivery or performance by such Party of this Agreement (A) will contravene its governing documents, (B) will contravene or violate any applicable Law in any material respect or (C) will violate or result in a default or breach under any agreement or instrument binding upon such Party or its assets, in each case, in any material respect.
(b) Subject to the terms of this Agreement, Lessor agrees that (i) whenever Lessor has an obligation with respect to the Undivided Interest, then, to the extent such obligation, consent or approval relates to the Shared Assets or Lessees use and occupation thereof, Lessor will perform such obligation; and (ii) Lessor shall not, in the exercise of any of the rights arising or which may arise out of this Agreement or the SFA, or of any instrument modifying or amending the same or entered into in substitution or replacement thereof, disturb or deprive Lessee in, or of, its rights with respect to the Undivided Interest or of any right or privilege granted to or inuring to the benefit of Lessee under this Agreement.
(c) Lessor represents and warrants, as of the Effective Date, that (i) the SFA and the Shared Premises Agreements are in full force and effect, and Lessor is not in breach of any of the Shared Premises Agreements, nor are there any events which would constitute breaches or defaults under the Shared Premises Agreements upon receipt of notice or the passage of time (ii) Lessor has not previously assigned or subleased its Undivided Interest or its Percentage Interest, each as granted pursuant to the SFA, (iii) Lessor has not received any notice of any pending or threatened condemnation proceeding, zoning change or legal, regulatory or other noncompliance relating to the Shared Premises, (iv) the Shared Premises is free from any recorded or unrecorded use or occupancy restrictions of declarations of restrictive covenants that would not allow the Shared Premises to be used for its intended purposes, (v) Lessor is not in the hands of a receiver nor is an application for such a receiver pending, nor has Lessor made an assignment for the benefit of creditors, nor has Lessor filed, or had filed against it, any petition in bankruptcy, nor is Lessor insolvent, (vi) Lessor is not a defendant in any ongoing or pending litigation proceedings that would have a material adverse effect on the Undivided Interest or Percentage Interest, (vii) to the best knowledge of Lessor, the Shared Premises is in compliance with all laws, including, but not limited to, Environmental.
5 Docusign Envelope ID: 5F8783FD-559A-46EF-A7B0-4208ED99724F
Lessor covenants that it will keep the Shared Premises free from use or occupancy restrictions of declarations of restrictive covenants that would not allow the Shared Premises to be used for its intended purposes.
(d) EXCEPT FOR THE REPRESENTATIONS AND WARRANTIES CONTAINED IN THIS SECTION 7, NEITHER PARTY HAS MADE OR MAKES ANY OTHER EXPRESS OR IMPLIED REPRESENTATIONS OR WARRANTIES, EITHER WRITTEN OR ORAL, AND EACH PARTY EXPRESSLY DISCLAIMS AND NEGATES, AND NEITHER PARTY HAS RELIED UPON, ANY OTHER REPRESENTATION OR WARRANTY, EXPRESS, STATUTORY, IMPLIED, OR OTHERWISE, INCLUDING MERCHANTABILITY OR FITNESS FOR PURPOSE.
8. Non-Recourse. No past, present or future director, officer, employee, incorporator, direct or indirect member, partner, stockholder, manager, financing source, lender, agent, attorney, representative or Affiliate of either Party or of any of their respective Affiliates shall have any Liability (whether in contract or in tort or otherwise) arising under, in connection with, or related to, this Agreement, INCLUDING ANY LIABILITY ARISING FROM THE JOINT, SOLE, GROSS OR CONCURRENT NEGLIGENCE THEREOF; provided, however, that nothing in this Section 8 shall limit any Liability of the Parties. Each Party hereby waives, and shall cause each of its Affiliates to waive, any such Liability.
9. Term; FERC. This Agreement shall commence on the Effective Date and continue until the expiration or termination of the SFA (Term). This Agreement may not be terminated earlier than the expiration of the Term for any reason, other than in connection with the exercise of any remedies under the Security Documents. The Parties shall, if required pursuant to FERCs regulations or other applicable Law, file this Agreement with FERC under Section 205 of the Federal Power Act (the FERC Filing). The Parties shall not make the FERC Filing unless each Party has reviewed and approved the form and content of the FERC Filing, which approval will not be unreasonably withheld, denied or delayed. For purposes of the FERC Filing, this Agreement shall become effective on the later to occur of (a) the Effective Date and (b) the effective date designated by FERC when this Agreement is accepted for filing by FERC.
10. Force Majeure. Article 10 of the SFA is hereby incorporated in this Agreement, mutatis mutandis. If a Party has the right to declare Force Majeure under Article 10 of the SFA and so declares Force Majeure in accordance therewith, such Party shall be excused of its obligations hereunder to the extent such obligations correspond to obligations under the SFA.
11. Indemnity.
(a) Lessee Indemnity to Lessor. Lessee hereby releases and shall indemnify, defend and hold harmless Lessor, its successors and permitted assigns, its members, officers, directors, employees and agents, and their respective successors and permitted assigns (the Lessor Indemnitees) from and against any and all Liabilities incurred by such Lessor Indemnitees, to the extent the Liabilities arise out of (i) the gross negligence or willful misconduct of Lessee, its agents, employees or contractors; or (ii) in connection with the Project, this Agreement, the SFA or any Shared Premises Agreement (including the withholding of any consent or approval or prevention of any performance or payment required thereunder), INCLUDING ANY CLAIMS ARISING FROM THE JOINT, SOLE OR CONCURRENT NEGLIGENCE THEREOF; provided, that, in either case of Clause (i) or (ii), such Liabilities do not result from the gross negligence or willful misconduct of Lessor or its agents, employees or contractors.
(b) Lessor Indemnity to Lessee. Lessor hereby releases and shall indemnify, defend and hold harmless Lessee, its successors and permitted assigns, its members, officers, directors, employees and agents, and their respective successors and permitted assigns (the Lessee Indemnitees) from and against
6 Docusign Envelope ID: 5F8783FD-559A-46EF-A7B0-4208ED99724F
any and all Liabilities incurred by Lessee Indemnitees, to the extent the Liabilities arise out of the gross negligence or willful misconduct of Lessor, its agents, contractors or employees, INCLUDING ANY CLAIMS ARISING FROM THE JOINT, SOLE OR CONCURRENT NEGLIGENCE THEREOF; provided, that such Liabilities do not arise from the gross negligence or willful misconduct of Lessee or its agents, contractors or employees.
12. Insurance. Each Party shall maintain all of the insurance required of such Party under the SFA.
13. Casualty and Condemnation. A Party who receives any notice of a Casualty Event or Condemnation Event shall promptly give the other Party a copy of the notice, and each Party shall provide to the other Party copies of all subsequent notices or information received with respect to such Casualty Event or Condemnation Event, as applicable.
14. Events of Default.
(a) Events of Default. The occurrence of any one of the following shall constitute an event of default with respect to a Party hereunder (Event of Default):
(i) Failure to make any payment by a Party when due and such failure shall continue uncured for ten days after written notice thereof by the non-defaulting Party is delivered to the defaulting Party;
(ii) Failure of any representation or warranty made in this Agreement by a Party to be true and correct in all material respects, and such failure shall continue uncured for 30 days after written notice thereof by the non-defaulting Party is delivered to the defaulting Party; provided, however, that, if the defaulting Party is using commercially reasonable efforts to pursue such cure and such failure is not capable of being cured within such period of 30 days with the exercise of commercially reasonable efforts, then such cure period shall be extended for an additional reasonable period of time (not to exceed 180 days from delivery of such written notice) so long as the defaulting Party is exercising commercially reasonable efforts to cure such failure; and
(iii) Any other breach of this Agreement by a Party and such breach shall continue uncured for 30 days after written notice thereof by the non-defaulting Party is delivered to the defaulting Party; provided, however, that, if the defaulting Party is using commercially reasonable efforts to pursue such cure and such breach is not capable of being cured within such period of 30 days with the exercise of commercially reasonable efforts, then such cure period shall be extended for an additional reasonable period of time (not to exceed 180 days from delivery of such written notice) so long as the defaulting Party is exercising commercially reasonable efforts to cure such breach; provided, however, that, in the case of Clauses (i)-(iii), the cure periods provided in this Section 14(a) shall be shortened to the extent necessary to prevent any corresponding default or exercise of remedies under the Interconnection Agreement, any applicable power purchase or energy storage agreement, the SFA or any Shared Premises Agreement.
(b) Remedies. Upon the occurrence and during the continuation of an Event of Default, any non-defaulting Party shall have the right to any and all remedies under this Agreement, at law or in equity; provided, however, that (i) if Lessee is subject to an Event of Default that is continuing, Lessor may suspend any rights of Lessee under this Agreement, (ii) neither Party may terminate this Agreement prior to the expiration of the Term, and (iii) if such Event of Default is by Lessor and is continuing, Lessee shall be permitted to exercise its rights under the Security Documents, including the right to step-in to the rights and obligations of Lessor under the SFA.
7 Docusign Envelope ID: 5F8783FD-559A-46EF-A7B0-4208ED99724F
15. Assignment and Subletting.
(a) Neither Party shall have the right to assign any of its rights, duties or obligations under this Agreement without the prior written consent of the other Party; provided, however, that (i) if Lessee assigns its interest in the Project, Lessee shall assign its interest under this Agreement, and (ii) each Party may, without consent, collaterally assign its interest in this Agreement and in the Project, the SFA, the Shared Premises Agreements and the Shared Assets, as applicable, as provided in Section 16.
(b) No consent by either Party to any assignment or delegation by the other Party shall be deemed to be a novation or otherwise to relieve the assigning Party of its obligations hereunder unless otherwise expressly so stated in such consent.
(c) This Agreement will be binding upon and inure to the benefit of the Parties and their respective successors and permitted assigns. Nothing in this Agreement, expressed or implied, is intended or will be construed to confer upon any Person (other than the Parties and successors and assigns permitted by this Section 15) any right, remedy or claim under or by reason of this Agreement. Any assignment in breach of this Section 15 shall be void.
16. Project Financing. Each Party may, from time to time and at any time, without the consent of the other Party, hypothecate, mortgage, pledge or alienate all or any portion of its interest under this Agreement, the SFA, the Shared Premises Agreement, the Project and the Shared Assets to any Person (or its agent), as applicable, providing financing for the development, construction or operation of the Project or the Shared Assets, as applicable. Except as provided in the Security Documents, nothing herein shall be deemed to permit a Financing Party of Lessee to take title to, or otherwise encumber, Lessors fee title or other interest in the Undivided Interest or Percentage Interest. Each Party shall cooperate with the other Partys Financing Parties and their advisors and consultants and shall make all information, reports, logs and other documents relating to the Project or the Shared Assets, as applicable, available to such Financing Parties and their advisors and consultants. Each Party also shall, at any time and from time to time, after receipt of a written request by the other Party, execute and deliver to such Party or any Financing Parties thereof, any consents to collateral assignments, officers certificates, opinions or other information or document as such Financing Parties may reasonably request. Each Party shall provide in their respective financing agreements that if any Financing Parties thereof foreclose on any interest granted under the Security Documents, such Financing Parties shall assume the obligations under this Agreement.
17. Remedies Cumulative; Specific Performance. Except as provided herein, no remedy herein conferred upon or reserved to Lessor and Lessee shall exclude any other remedy herein or by law provided, but each shall be cumulative and in addition to every other remedy given hereunder or now or hereafter existing at law or in equity or by statute. Each Party acknowledges and agrees that the other Party may be damaged irreparably in the event that such Partys obligations under this Agreement are not performed in accordance with their specific terms or are otherwise breached or threatened to be breached, that the remedies at law for any such breach or threatened breach, including monetary damages, might be inadequate compensation for any loss as a result thereof, and that any defense in any action for specific performance that a remedy at law would be adequate is waived. Accordingly, each Party agrees, on behalf of itself, its Affiliates and its and their respective Representatives, that the other Party shall be entitled to seek specific performance and other equitable relief to enforce specifically the provisions of this Agreement or to prevent such non-performance or other breach or threatened breach of such provisions (without having to post any bond or other security), in addition to any rights or remedies permitted under this Agreement.
18. Relationship of the Parties. Neither the execution nor delivery of this Agreement, nor the consummation of the transactions contemplated hereunder, shall create or constitute a partnership, joint venture, trust, limited liability company, corporate or any other form of business organization or
8 Docusign Envelope ID: 5F8783FD-559A-46EF-A7B0-4208ED99724F
arrangement between the Parties. Neither Party (or any of its agents, officers or employees) shall be an agent or employee of the other Party, nor shall a Party (or any of its agents, officers or employees) have any power to bind, assume or create any obligation on behalf of the other Party. LESSEE HEREBY WAIVES ANY DUTY OR NON-CONTRACTUAL CLAIM (WHETHER STATUTORY, TORT OR FIDUCIARY) ARISING IN CONNECTION WITH THIS AGREEMENT, EXCEPT FOR A BREACH OF THE EXPRESS PROVISIONS OF THIS AGREEMENT.
19. Miscellaneous Provisions.
(a) Notices. All notices and other communications required or permitted by this Agreement or by applicable Law to be served upon or given to a Party by the other Party shall be in writing and shall be deemed duly served, given and received (i) on the date of service, if served personally, or (ii) on date of receipt, if mailed by certified mail, postage prepaid, return receipt requested, or (iii) on the date of receipt if sent by a nationally recognized courier for next day service and so addressed as follows or as the Parties otherwise agreed in writing:
If to Lessor, to:
